</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uwyvernwyrmsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyvern Wyrmsong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/11/01 9:29:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mitch</span><hr size=1> A legal evaluation:<br>
<br>
*But your honor, I only stole one copy of Windows from Bill Gates.  He has $5 billion dollars and makes the software.*  That defense doesn't work.  Just ask any business who was sued for using unlicensed software. So we can see the value of the bracer is irrelevant to this issue.<br>
<br>
Mitch admits he has/had the bracer.  That is not in dispute.  Numerous quotes are on record where Mitch threatens the bracer will be dropped on a newbie mob, or otherwise destroyed as a penalty to Areosa, thus implying she has the bracer.  No where is the defense of never having the bracer. Therefore, Mitch has, or had, the bracer.<br>
<br>
Mitch thought the bracer was a gift.  Areosa did not.  One must look to the intent of the giver at the time of the giving.  Taking Areosa's comments as posted by Mitch, the statement *I will need to replace it sometime* indicates he expected to get that bracer or another one of similar usefulness back, or alternatively, help from Mitch in obtaining another one.  From the context, it appears the bracer was on a character Areo was not playing as much at that time (her bard), and she thought Mitch would get more present use out of the bracer.  This is not an uncommon action between guildmates and friends. &quot;Take this, it is on my twink.  I will need to replace it sometime &quot; (i.e. when I play this character and not the one I use for now)  Areo is now playing the character that had the bracer, and wishes for it, or a reasonable replacement back.<br>
<br>
The reply of Mitch is something to the effect of &quot;I will happily help you camp another one.&quot;  This transaction of *take something now, in exchange for a promise of future action* is not a gift, but rather a unilateral contract.  An item for a promise.  Specifically, an exchange of an item for a promise of return or service at a later date.  Areosa agreed to the giving of the item with the expectation of receiving the item, or help obtaining another one, back from Mitch.<br>
<br>
She attempts to reach Mitch via tells.  Mitch is apparently busy in ToV one time.  Another time Mitch does not mention where she is.  I know Areo complained Mitch was avoiding her more than on just those two occassions.  Irregardless, even a single reply of &quot;Busy now, talk to me later.&quot;  might have eased Areo's concern of default on the contract.  Complete inaction, and ignoring the reception of the tells would make the giver reasonably concerned of default on the contract.  If a bank gives a loan, and the person refuses to answer calls and letters made to them concerning the loan, a bank will start to get suspicious of repayment.  Even a courtesy call saying I will have your money, can help relieve these concerns.<br>
<br>
This did not happen here, so Areo resorted to an area of public forum where she complained Mitch is avoiding her and refuses to give the bracer back.  Mitch complains Areo is libeling him (Note slander is verbal defamation, libel is defamation in a permanent i.e. printed or published medium)  Truth is an absolute defense to both libel and slander.  Here it seems the facts are undisputed that Mitch had a bracer and refuses to give it back.  There is perhaps a claim of libel lies in the statements of Areo that Mitch stole things from AoR when she left.  As there are no statements on this record concerning that claim, one cannot assess the truth or libelous nature of this statement.<br>
<br>
The destruction, or dispersal of the property without adequate replacement would be a default of the contract.  Given the nature of the comments, it seems Mitch is not inclined to help AreoX camp a replacement bracer, so this option of the contract is also defaulted. As with all disputes, things could usually be handled in a better manner.  Most disputes are not amicable, and typically both parties do something less than perfect.  In this case, it seems that Areo was within his rights to ask for acknowledgment of the contract.  Receiving no response at all, much less even acknowledgment of the agreements existence, Areo felt he was being avoided, and thus came to a forum where at least the desired action of getting Mitch's attention was achieved.<br>
<br>
I am a current guildmate of AreoX.  However, I feel that my analysis above is objective.  I have no ill feelings toward Mitch and have in fact grouped or been on raids with him before, with no problems.  As I have no power of law in EQ obviosuly, the above represents nothing more than my opinion, but it is based upon the rules of common law tradition that exist in both the UK and the USA. If you have not figured it out, I have a law degree, and a member of a state Bar.<br>
<br>
-Wyvern<br>
58 Troubadour<br>
&lt;Institute&gt;<br>
<br>
P.S. as for the BMW issues, BMW is a German based company trading in the German exchange.  Rolls Royce and Land Rover (British auto manifacturers) were purchased by BMW in the past.  BMW in turn liquidated Land Rover and Rover Cars to Ford, Inc. within the last year.  Thus, BMW is German, but owned some British car manifacturers, who then sold those British manufacturers to a US maker.  Simple enough, don't know why anyone was confused by that. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/upurtyogre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>purtyogre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/11/01 9:30:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.swordsofhonor.com/lib/greatsword/warrior WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mitch</span><hr size=1> WOW the first honorable and classy thing said.<br>
